%% Related documentation: ../authentication.md; ../endpoints/authentication-and-session.md
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Browser
    participant AuthRoutes as Public Auth Routes
    participant Tokens as JWT and Refresh Token Service
    participant Database
    participant Protected as Protected Router

    Browser->>AuthRoutes: Register or login JSON
    AuthRoutes->>Database: Validate or create active user and memberships
    AuthRoutes->>Tokens: Issue access and refresh tokens
    Tokens->>Database: Store hashed refresh token
    AuthRoutes-->>Browser: AuthResponse and HttpOnly refresh cookie

    Browser->>Protected: Authorization Bearer access token
    Protected->>Tokens: Validate access token
    Tokens-->>Protected: Claims
    Protected-->>Browser: Protected response

    Browser->>AuthRoutes: Refresh cookie or JSON refresh token
    AuthRoutes->>Database: Validate and revoke prior refresh record
    AuthRoutes->>Tokens: Rotate token pair
    AuthRoutes-->>Browser: New AuthResponse and refresh cookie

    Browser->>Protected: Logout with bearer token and refresh token source
    Protected->>Database: Revoke refresh token when supplied
    Protected-->>Browser: LogoutResponse and cleared cookie
